e> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Barrick Gold has been ordered to pay vetera=
n dealmaker Ian Hannam=E2=80=99s firm $2mn plus legal costs after the High =
Court in London found his advisory boutique helped engineer a $6bn merger a=
nd failed to be compensated.</p> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hannam &amp; =
Partners had demanded up to $18mn from the Canadian mining group, claiming =
it was central to a transformational combination in 2018 between Barrick an=
d London-listed Randgold but that it was =E2=80=9Cpushed out=E2=80=9D of th=
e deal at the last minute. =E2=80=A6</p> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In a =
lengthy judgment on Wednesday, Judge Simon Gleeson found H &amp; P had secu=
red no legally binding agreement for fees on the deal. Even so, he ruled in=
 its favour on a legal principle known as unjust enrichment.</p> <p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Speaking after the ruling, Hannam said: =E2=80=9CMy wo=
rd is my bond is still at the heart of a client relationship.=E2=80=9D He s=
aid the judge had =E2=80=9Cunderlined the tenets of this relationship, whic=
h have existed in the City of London for centuries=E2=80=9D. =E2=80=A6</p> =
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The judge cited specific instances of work con=
ducted by H &amp; P, including a =E2=80=9Cstoryboard=E2=80=9D presentation =
that set out a rationale for a Barrick acquisition of Randgold. Gleeson als=
o noted Hannam acted as a =E2=80=9Cgo-between=E2=80=9D between [then-Randgo=
ld CEO Mark]=C2=A0Bristow and Barrick=E2=80=99s [John] Thornton, a former G=
oldman Sachs president who now chairs the enlarged group.=C2=A0</p> </block=
quote> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You can=E2=80=99t really get a=C2=A0<em=
>whole=C2=A0</em>M&amp;A fee unless the client actually mandates you on the=
 deal, but if you really did a lot of the deal maybe you should get=C2=A0<e=
m>something</em>. The=C2=A0judge also has this extremely elegant descriptio=
n of M&amp;A banking:</p> <blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=
=9CInvestment bankers, like teenage lovers, pour out their efforts, almost =
without limit and in response to the slightest encouragement in the hope of=
 reaching the nirvana of a mandate,=E2=80=9D the judge wrote.</p></blockquo=
te> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Right like if Barrick had told Hannam from=
 the start =E2=80=9Cyou should drop everything to work on this deal, but we=
